                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> DUNSTEW. <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> de <surname>Donestiva</surname>
                        </persName> grants to 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Stephen</forename> the priest of <placeName role="priest" key="place_109412">Orton</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>,
               two virgates of land in <placeName key="place_109257">Donestiva</placeName> with appurtenances, one of which 2 virgates the
               said Stephen the priest held of the grantor which is of his demesne, together with a
               messuage near the house of <persName>
                           <forename>Wimund</forename>
                        </persName>, paying annually for
               the same 3s.; and the other virgate that <persName>
                           <forename>Ailwin</forename>
                        </persName> held, which 
               the said Stephen gave to <persName>
                           <forename>Emma</forename> mother of Peter</persName>, and is now
               held by the said Peter, paying annually also 3s. For this grant the said Peter gave
               one mark of silver. 
               (<origDate when="1200" precision="low">c. 1200</origDate>.) 
               .
            </p>
